The United States has expressed disappointment with the Government of South Sudan for not signing the peace agreement. The US appreciates the efforts of the Intergovernmental Authority on Development (IGAD) leaders in supporting the talks and urges the Government of South Sudan to sign the agreement within the agreed 15 days. The US also emphasizes that there must be consequences for those who hinder the peace process and has initiated consultations at the United Nations and with international partners on possible sanctions.